    <h1 align="center">@@pkg@@ - a pro-active password library</h1>

    <p>
      <code>@@pkg@@</code> is a library containing a C function which may be
      used in a <a
      href="/cgi-bin/man2html/usr/man/man1/passwd.1.gz"><code>passwd</code></a>
      like program.  The idea is simple: try to prevent users from choosing
      passwords that could be guessed by <a
      href="@@url_pkg_dir@@"><code>crack</code></a> by filtering them out, at
      source. <code>@@pkg@@</code> is <em>not</em> a replacement <a
      href="/cgi-bin/man2html/usr/man/man1/passwd.1.gz"><code>passwd</code></a>
      program.  <code>@@pkg@@</code> is a <em>library</em>.
    </p>

    <p>
      <code>@@pkg@@</code> is an offshoot of version 5 of the <a
      href="@@url_pkg_dir@@"><code>crack</code></a> software and contains a
      considerable number of ideas nicked from the new software.
    </p>

    <p>
      <code>@@pkg@@</code>'s <a href="@@url_pkg_dir@@">home page</a> provides
      some links on security publications and access to source code written by
      the author of <code>@@pkg@@</code>.  While there is a <a
      href="README">README</a> there is not much documentation available on
      <code>@@pkg@@</code>.  Hopefully this page that I generated for the <a
      href="http://www.debian.org">Debian/GNU Linux</a> distribution will
      improved this situation.
    </p>


