    <h2>
      <a name="cracklib.debian.package">Debian <code>@@pkg@@</code> package
      overview.</a>
    </h2>

    <p>
      The source package is <code>@@pkg@@</code> which generates the following
      binary packages:
    </p>

    <dl>
      <dt><code>@@pkg@@</code></dt>
      <dd>
        Shared library and all documentation except for the example program.
      </dd>

      <dt><code>cracklib2-dev</code></dt>
      <dd>
        Header files, static libraries, documentation, and symbolic links
        developers using <code>@@pkg@@</code> will need.
      </dd>

      <dt><code>cracklib-runtime</code></dt>
      <dd>
        Run-time support programs which use the shared library in
        <code>@@pkg@@</code> including programs to build the password
        dictionary databases used by the functions in the shared library.
      </dd>
    </dl>

    <p>
      I have not include a <a href="#cracklib.dictionaries">dictionary</a> with
      this source package.  I plan to add one when I package <a
      href="@@url_pkg_dir@@"><code>crack</code></a>.
    </p>


